    "narrative": "Our lineup today is anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (74.41) and **Trea Turner** (70.46), who stand out as our elite producers against favorable matchups. **Yordan Alvarez** faces Cecconi with a strong 0.393 xwOBA, buoyed by a significant platoon advantage and a premium spot in the two-hole. **Trea Turner** remains our primary catalyst against Colin Rea; while the matchup against a high-hold-rate pitcher suppresses his stolen base ceiling slightly, his top-of-the-order positioning makes him a foundational start. Similarly, **Kyle Schwarber** (69.69) is a high-conviction play against Rea, leveraging an elite 0.402 xwOBA to maximize our Home Run and RBI output.\n\nStrategic upside is also evident in **Hyeseong Kim** (60.67) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (60.48). Despite their assumed #8 spots, both benefit from favorable opposing SP skill metrics. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** specifically draws a +14% boost from a dynamic platoon edge against Nola, which outweighs the risk posed by the pitcher's elite catch-and-throw metrics. On the bench, **Dillon Dingler** (36.09) was the most difficult exclusion; despite a +7% park factor, his sub-40 efficiency score\u2014dragged down by a poor platoon matchup against Gray\u2014fell just below our threshold for active roster status. We are closely monitoring the lineup postings for **Hyeseong Kim**, **Kazuma Okamoto**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, and **Luke Raley**, as these assumed positions are critical to maintaining our projected efficiency across the 5x5 categories. While **Victor Scott II** (43.77) remains in the lineup for his defensive and speed contributions, he remains a marginal start today due to the bottom-of-the-order penalty and a lack of SP vulnerability.",
